       <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.schelp.co.uk/blog/?p=503</guid> 
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This post is number four of an occasional six part series on my personal values and principles;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://scottinbrief.blogspot.com/2006/09/practice-being-different.html&#34;&gt;read post one&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://scottinbrief.blogspot.com/2006/10/dont-be-bothered-by-fears-values-and.html&#34;&gt;read post two&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://scottinbrief.blogspot.com/2006/10/love-extravagantly-values-and.html&#34;&gt;read post three&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://scottinbrief.blogspot.com/2006/11/be-last-put-others-first-values-and.html&#34;&gt;read post four&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://bp0.blogger.com/_AQL5BvjF3p8/Ra7Bjn_KjOI/AAAAAAAAABo/oDLr786_gL8/s1600-h/bsg_number.six.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;http://bp0.blogger.com/_AQL5BvjF3p8/Ra7Bjn_KjOI/AAAAAAAAABo/oDLr786_gL8/s320/bsg_number.six.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
seeing and being seen,&lt;br&gt;
hearing and being heard,&lt;br&gt;
being moved by others and allowing others to be moved by us&lt;br&gt;
responding with acts of kindness and recieving acts of kindness&lt;br&gt;
Embodying a sense of delight in all our interactions.&lt;br&gt;
(Mark Yaconelli, Contemplative Youth Ministry)
Thats what I guess I am trying to get to.
Not sure how am getting on, but trying.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
